description: Voltage-gated sodium potassium channel (Na). Other names for this protein: NaV1.1 to 1.9, fastNaThe Na channel is thought to be made of one type of pore-forming alpha subunit, modulated by one or more beta subunits.

name: CellML model of Hydrogen-potassium ATPase (HKE)
description: This ATPase exchanges potassium ion entry for the extrusion of one hydrogen ion from the cell, at the expense of one ATP molecule being hydrolysed. The bond-graph model is illustrated in the figure below, with the CellML model added for simulation purposes.

name: CellML model of Inositol triphosphate receptor

name: CellML model of plasma membrane calcium-transporting ATPase (PMCA)
description: Its major function is to catalyze the hydrolysis of ATP coupled with the extrusion of calcium from the cytoplasm to the extracellular space.

name: CellML model of sodium-driven chloride-bicarbonate exchanger
description: This exchanger allows entry of a sodium ion and two bicarbonate ions in exchange for the extrusion of one chloride ion from the cell.

name: CellML model of the ABC channel operating under normal physiological conditions
description: The ATPase Binding Cassette (ABC) transporter superfamily is made of proteins can either import or export substrates from the cell. It uses ATP to perform the action, where the stoichiometry of ATP used will vary depending on the type of ABC. Substrates transported range from ions to macromolecules.

name: CellML model of the sodium bicarbonate cotransporter
description: This transporter allows entry of one sodium ion in conjunction with 2 bicarbonate ions into the cell. The bond-graph model is illustrated in the figure below, with the CellML model added for simulation purposes.

name: CellML model of the L-type calcium pump CaL.
description: CaLs are multisubunit complexes, consisting of a combination of alpha, beta, gamma and delta subunits. The channel activity is generally directed by the pore-forming and voltage-sensitive alpha subunit.

name: CellML model of Sodium calcium exchanger
description: This transporter allows entry of 3 sodium ions, in exchange for the extrusion of one calcium ion. The bond-graph model is illustrated in the figure below, with the CellML model added for simulation purposes.

name: CellML model of sodium potassium exchanger
description: This transporter allows entry of two potassium ion in exchange for the extrusion of three sodium ions from the cell, at the expense of ATP being hydrolysed to release energy for the process.

name: CellML model of calcium buffer troponin
description: Calcium is bound reversibly to troponin molecules in order to control the intracellular calcium concentration.

name: CellML model of inhibitor-1 (Inhib1)
description: Inhibitor-1 can be a potent inhibitor of protein phosphatase-1 (PP1), participating in reactions involving PKA.

name: CellML model of T-type calcium pump CaT.
description: CaT allows for calcium entry into the cell and is responsible for helping trigger muscle contraction predominantly within cardiac, skeletal and smooth muscle cells. T-type calcium channels belong to the 'low-voltage activated (LVA)' group. Normally closed, this type of channel opens at quite negative potentials and has voltage-dependent inactivation, the latter achieved during cell hyperpolarisation. Gating of this channel is also voltage-dependent.CaT are made of a primary alpha subunit that forms the pore. As in other calcium channels, there may also be beta, gamma, and delta auxiliary subunits that are involved in channel regulation, but are likely absent from CaT.Most reactions follow Michaelis-Menten kinetics, where an intermediate complex is made before the final product is created (e.g. Re:1a and Re:1b). All other reactions (Re5-8) follow classical mass-action kinetics.

name: CellML model of cyclic AMP (cAMP) and adenylyl cyclase (AC) metabolism in the cardiac cell.
description: This model is made from an existing kinetic model, where the mathematics are translated into the bond-graph formalism. This describes the model in energetic terms and forces adherence to the laws of thermodynamics.Most reactions follow Michaelis-Menten kinetics, where an intermediate complex is made before the final product is created (e.g. Re:1a and Re:1b). All other reactions (Re5-8) follow classical mass-action kinetics.

name: CellML model of receptor tyrosine kinase (RTK)
description: This is a bond-graph model of the metabolism of generic receptor tyrosine kinase (RTK) in the mammalian cell.

name: CellML model of Kp
description: Kp protein

name: CellML model of protein kinase A (PKA)
description: PKA is a key regulator of normal cell function in various organs in the body. It is activated by cAMP action, and is inhibited by PKI.

name: CellML model of sodium hydrogen exchanger
description: This transporter allows entry of one sodium ion in exchange for the extrusion of one hydrogen ion from the cell.

name: CellML model of the pacemaker channel HCN (potassium/sodium hyperpolarization-activated cyclic nucleotide-gated channel).
description: The pacemaker channel HCN (potassium/sodium hyperpolarization-activated cyclic nucleotide-gated channel). This channel creates the pacemaker current, also known as the funny current.The HCN group is highly expressed in cardiac myocytes in order to generate action potentials for establishing heart beats. It is permeable to both potassium and sodium ions, with preference for potassium.HCN is thought to be a homotetramer, where the channel is composed of a homo- or heterotetrameric complex of pore-forming subunits. It is activated by membrane hyperpolarisation, and all subfamilies except HCN3 are also activated by cAMP binding to their cyclic nucleotide binding domain.

name: CellML model of potassium delayed rectifier channel
description: This channels is known to transport potassium across the plasma membrane according to the concentration gradient. In cardiac cells, it is integral to the formation and maintenance of the action potential.

name: CellML model of slow delayed rectifier potassium channel
description: This channels is known to transport potassium across the plasma membrane according to the concentration gradient. In cardiac cells, it is integral to the formation and maintenance of the action potential.

name: CellML model of transient outward potassium current
description: This channel transports potassium ions across the plasma membrane according to the concentration gradient. It is crucial in the early repolarisation of the cell membrane during the cardiac action potential, as it rapidly activates and inactivates following membrane depolarization.

name: CellML model of the SLC family: AE3 (SLC4A3)
description: The Anion exchanger - chloride bicarbonate transporter allows entry of a chloride ion in exchange for the extrusion of one bicarbonate ion from the cell. The bond-graph model is illustrated in the figure below, with the CellML model added for simulation purposes.

name: CellML model of the membrane proteins constituting the background calcium current (CaB)
description: Model of the cardiomyocyte maintaining calcium homeostasis, by counterbalancing the extrusion of calcium from the cytosol through the NCX.

name: CellML model of sodium potassium exchanger
description: This transporter allows entry of two potassium ion in exchange for the extrusion of three sodium ions from the cell, at the expense of ATP being hydrolysed to release energy for the process.

name: CellML model of transport of glucose and sodium through the SGLT1 transporter
description: This example is designed to show electrogenic cotransport through the SGLT1 (SLC5A1) transporter, transporting one glucose molecule into the small intestine, coupled with two sodium ions.

name: CellML model of soluble guanylyl cyclase enzyme (sGC)
description: Nitric oxide in the cytoplasm activates sGC, towards relaxing the smooth muscle cell.

name: CellML model of ATPase pumps: Calcium ATPase (SERCA)
description: This ATPase pumps out 2 calcium ions from the sarcoplasmic reticulum, and one hydrogen ion enters. For this process, one ATP molecule is hydrolysed.

name: CellML model of role of cyclic guanosine monophosphate (cGMP) in muscle relaxation
description: cGMP is an integral messenger, for pathways involved with vascular smooth muscle relaxation.This model is derived from Yang et. al

name: CellML model of K ATP
description: Potassium ATP protein.

name: CellML model of ryanodine receptor (Ryr)
description: Its major function is to create calcium-induced calcium release (CICR): the channel mediates the release of calcium from the sarcoplasmic reticulum into the cytosol, leading to the triggering of muscle contraction following depolarization of T-tubules in the same cell.

name: CellML model of the chloride hydroxide exchanger (CHE).
description: This exchanger transports hydroxide ions into the cell in exchange for the extrusion of chloride ions.

name: CellML model of the SLC family: EAAT2 (SLC1A2)
description: The glutamate transporter allows entry of glutamate coupled with 3 sodium and one hydrogen ion, in exchange for one potassium ion expelled from the cell. The bond-graph model is illustrated in the figure below, with the CellML model added for simulation purposes.

name: CellML model of phospholamban (PLB)
description: PLB inhibits the SERCA pump in its unphosphoryated state.

name: CellML model of the metabolism of the G-protein coupled receptor (muscarinic acetylcholine M2 receptor, R) and the associated Gi protein in the cardiac cell.
description: Original kinetic modelSaucerman et al: Modeling beta-adrenergic control of cardiac myocyte contractility in silico.Additional detail on receptor internalisation were provided by Stephen Duffull et al. (University of Otago).

name: CellML model of the ATPase pumps: Hydrogen ATPase (Proton pump)
description: This ATPase pumps one hydrogen ion out of the cell, at the expense of one ATP molecule being hydrolysed. The bond-graph model is illustrated in the figure below, with the CellML model added for simulation purposes.

name: CellML model of cardiac G-protein coupled receptor
description: bond-graph model of the metabolism of the G-protein coupled receptor (Î²-1 adrenergic receptor, R) and the associated Gs protein in the cardiac cell.

name: CellML model of ligand binding a receptor
description: This is a bond-graph model of a ligand binding a receptor on the cell surface and forming an activated complex. The corresponding G protein is also involved.

name: Gene Set Foundation Model
description: Trained on millions of gene sets automatically extracted from literature and raw RNA-seq data, GSFM learns to recover held-out genes from gene sets. The resulting model exhibits state-of-the-art performance on gene function prediction.

name: HuBMAP Data Portal
description: The HuBMAP Data Portal is the central resource for discovery, visualization, and download of single-cell tissue data generated by the consortium. A standardized data curation and processing workflow ensure that only high quality is released.
